{
  "stem": "20142.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were, we were fortunate we got some little marmalade, or at 12 o'clock, when we got the soup there was watery substance, with leaves and a few potatoes floating.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "On the way back from work at 6 o'clock, and we got another portion of soup.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you were fortunate if you were one of the very first ones to have this soup distributed when the few potatoes were floating.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Or if they did like or did not like your face.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Is very hard to describe what-- what feeling you had when you looked at the soap.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You didn't know whether to wash yourself with it, or-- or to swallow it and eat it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How did people survive?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By encouraging each other, and giving [? each other ?] hope that tomorrow might be the end of the war, or maybe in a week, or so.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew that we had great hope.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That perhaps what happened at the beginning of 1941, when the Germans attacked Russia, that we knew about it already at the time, that this would not-- How did you know?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--prevail.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when we were working in-- for the Germans, and like [INAUDIBLE], we had crossing by a truck the streets of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew that the Russian prisons are being marched daily to show the population how did they look, how the Great Red Army looked.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a devastating sight of poorly dressed and with long coats, unusual hats.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Majority of them were of Asian [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] origin, like Mongols, Uzbeks, and [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the shoes that they were wearing, they were not shoes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were sort of a-- a combination [INAUDIBLE] made out of material, not the leather.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
